@SayGen102
"TS is an older rarer format that has no real purpose and should be questioned when seen."

This is not true. Look up what a TS(Transport Stream) is. It's simply a container that holds TV broadcast data, and captures the TV broadcast exactly as it aired, or exactly how you set your cable/satellite connection to the broadcast.


